---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Work Forest">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-badge">Open Source Pattern</div>
    <h1>Work Forest</h1>
    <p class="tagline">A pattern for parallel AI-assisted development</p>
    <p class="hero-desc">
      Work across multiple repositories simultaneously. Split complex tasks into focused pieces.
      Integrate scattered ideas. Extract shared patterns into libraries. All with AI agents
      working in parallel, isolated worktrees.
    </p>
    <div class="hero-cta">
      <a href="/patterns/work-forest" class="btn btn-primary">Get Started</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/joshribakoff/workforest.space" class="btn btn-secondary" target="_blank">
        View on GitHub
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="problems">
    <h2>Real Problems This Solves</h2>
    <div class="problem-list">
      <div class="problem">
        <div class="problem-scenario">"This feature is getting out of hand..."</div>
        <p>You started adding auth, now you're deep in database schemas, API routes, and React context all at once. <strong>Split it up.</strong> One agent handles the API, another the UI, a third the database. Work on each in isolation, integrate when ready.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="problem">
        <div class="problem-scenario">"I keep copying this code between projects..."</div>
        <p>Your three Astro sites all have the same theme toggle, the same nav component, the same patterns. <strong>Extract a library.</strong> One agent creates the package, others update each site to use it. Coordinated changes across repos.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="problem">
        <div class="problem-scenario">"I have five half-finished ideas..."</div>
        <p>Feature branches everywhere. Some work, some don't. Context is scattered. <strong>Consolidate with plans.</strong> Document what each branch does, what's blocking it, what depends on what. Pick up any thread without losing the others.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="problem">
        <div class="problem-scenario">"The agent's context window filled up mid-task..."</div>
        <p>You were making progress, then it forgot the earlier decisions. <strong>Plans survive resets.</strong> Decisions, rationale, and progress live in files. New sessions read the plan and continue where you left off.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="patterns">
    <h2>Patterns</h2>
    <div class="pattern-grid">
      <a href="/patterns/work-forest" class="pattern-card">
        <div class="pattern-icon">üå≤</div>
        <h3>Work Forest</h3>
        <p>Parallel worktrees across repos. See all in-flight work at a glance.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/patterns/work-clusters" class="pattern-card">
        <div class="pattern-icon">‚ö°</div>
        <h3>Work Clusters</h3>
        <p>Semantic grouping. Split, isolate, integrate. Work at higher abstraction.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/patterns/planning" class="pattern-card">
        <div class="pattern-icon">üìã</div>
        <h3>Planning Documents</h3>
        <p>Persistent context. Decisions that survive session resets.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/patterns/git-mechanics" class="pattern-card">
        <div class="pattern-icon">‚öôÔ∏è</div>
        <h3>Git Mechanics</h3>
        <p>Worktrees, submodules, dirty state. The git primitives underneath.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="quick-start">
    <h2>Quick Start</h2>
    <pre><code># You're working on site-a and site-b, both need the same component

# Create worktrees for the library and both sites
git worktree add ../my-lib -b extract-component
git worktree add ../site-a-update -b use-my-lib
git worktree add ../site-b-update -b use-my-lib

# Agents work in parallel:
# Agent 1: Extract component into my-lib
# Agent 2: Update site-a imports
# Agent 3: Update site-b imports

# Integration agent merges and verifies everything works</code></pre>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .hero {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 4rem 0 3rem;
  }

  .hero-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--accent);
    background: var(--accent-subtle);
    padding: 0.35rem 0.75rem;
    border-radius: 100px;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .hero h1 {
    font-size: 3.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--fg) 0%, var(--fg-muted) 50%, var(--accent) 100%);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
  }

  .tagline {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .hero-desc {
    max-width: 38rem;
    margin: 0 auto 2rem;
    color: var(--fg-subtle);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .hero-cta {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .btn {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    border-radius: 8px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: all 0.15s ease;
  }

  .btn-primary {
    background: var(--accent);
    color: var(--bg);
  }

  .btn-primary:hover {
    background: var(--fg);
    color: var(--bg);
  }

  .btn-secondary {
    background: var(--bg-elevated);
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .btn-secondary:hover {
    color: var(--fg);
    border-color: var(--fg-subtle);
  }

  .problems {
    padding: 2rem 0;
  }

  .problems h2 {
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .problem-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .problem {
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    background: var(--bg-elevated);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    border-radius: 10px;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
  }

  .problem-scenario {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--fg);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .problem p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .problem strong {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .patterns {
    padding: 2rem 0;
  }

  .patterns h2 {
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .pattern-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .pattern-card {
    display: block;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: var(--bg-elevated);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    border-radius: 12px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: all 0.2s ease;
  }

  .pattern-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--border);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .pattern-icon {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .pattern-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--fg);
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .pattern-card p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--fg-subtle);
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .quick-start {
    padding: 2rem 0 0;
  }

  .quick-start h2 {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .hero h1 {
      font-size: 2.5rem;
    }

    .pattern-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .hero-cta {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
    }

    .btn {
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 240px;
      justify-content: center;
    }
  }
</style>
